The paper discusses a machine learning method (Random Forest) and proposes a novel visualization technique (Self-Organising Maps) to better understand the model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Multidimensional Scaling (MDS) and compares the visualization of RF proximity matrix with MDS and SOM, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the classification accuracy of the SOM, suggesting that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with decision trees, which are a common data structure in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
